</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="45" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1436,471,1218]" pageId="2" pageNumber="45">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,338,1071,1097]" pageId="2" pageNumber="45">Discussion.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authority="Qin &amp; Zhang, 2007" authorityName="Qin &amp; Zhang" authorityYear="2007" box="[346,452,1072,1097]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Dayus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="45" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lii" status="n. sp.">
<emphasis box="[346,452,1072,1097]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="45">Dayus lii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[461,528,1071,1097]" pageId="2" pageNumber="45">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[461,528,1071,1097]" pageId="2" pageNumber="45" rank="species">n. sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
is similar to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Dworakowska" authorityYear="1971" box="[682,846,1072,1097]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Dayus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="45" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="takagii">
<emphasis box="[682,846,1072,1097]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="45">Dayus takagii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. It differs from the latter in its longer body length in male (
<quantity box="[256,350,1112,1138]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.2" pageId="2" pageNumber="45" unit="mm" value="4.2">4.2 mm</quantity>
compared to 
<quantity box="[515,639,1112,1138]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.05" metricValueMax="3.1" metricValueMin="3.0" pageId="2" pageNumber="45" unit="mm" value="3.05" valueMax="3.1" valueMin="3.0">3–3.1 mm</quantity>
), ventral pygofer appendage branched subapically, subgenital plate with 9 setae in basal group, nearly parallel-sided over its most part and aedeagal shaft with a pair of subapical bifurcate processes and another shorter pair of apical processes.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
